Google has launched the Street View experience to mark the 81st anniversary of the 'Surgeon's Photograph' - an image of the mythical monster from 1934 . 
  The image claimed to show evidence of a monster living in Loch Ness . 
  It was published in the Daily Mail on 21 April 1934 . 
  Google has also released a Google Doodle to commemorate the anniversary . 
  It lets you virtually explore both above and beneath the water in the iconic Scottish waterway . 
  Google partnered with the Loch Ness and Morar Project to capture the images . 
 